<p>was to move off at 8.a.m. So every was out in time &amp; at once got busy we got away up to time Some of the drivers had to make 3 trips in order to remove the Q.M. stores blankets &amp; officers kit &ndash; etc. The roads were very slippery and none of the horses had frost nails or cogs in their shoes, so we had to walk most of the way as the direct road was congested with traffic we had to go through Romarin  which made it a few miles further about 5 miles in all When I went to bed tonight some of the transports had not arrived at the camp, which is our old one viz South Hill Side Camp<br/> End of Year 1917</p>
